snippet: About 12.7 million people signed up for health coverage under the Affordable Care Act or had their coverage renewed in the third annual open enrollment season.
abstract: Health and Human Services Dept reports around 12.7 million people signed up for or renewed health insurance under Affordable Care Act during third open enrollment season since law’s passage; four million people who signed up were new to federal health insurance marketplace in 2016.
lead_paragraph: About 12.7 million people signed up for health coverage under the Affordable Care Act or had their coverage renewed in the third annual open enrollment season.

headline.main: Health Care Signups Exceed Hopes, With 4 Million Newcomers to Federal Marketplace
